The ✨Charlie’s Angels✨ of fermented toners 

Toners are my favourite skincare step, and I find myself constantly reaching for this trio! They tick all my boxes: great ingredients + ferments, hydrating, viscous texture, and they’re suitable for all skin types 🤍

🤎 @skin1004official probio cica essence toner is already well loved by the skincare community, and for good reasons! Formulated with fermented centella asiatica rich in probiotics, ceramide, and 5 sizes of hyaluronic acid, it’s deeply hydrating, calming, and perfect to strengthen and repair the skin barrier. Yet another skin1004 product worth the hype 

🐻 @axisy_official ay&me biome comforting infused toner contains a special biome blend of 5 different prebiotics and probiotics to promote general skin health and improve skin complexion, along with centella asiatica & mugwort to deeply soothe and calm irritated skin, and even ceramide to care for the skin barrier. If you haven’t tried it yet, you should! 

🧋 @kaine__official kombucha balancing ampoule toner, I finished my first bottle a couple months ago and let me tell you I MISSED IT SO MUCH! This baby has no less than 60% fermented kombucha packed in antioxidants, 1% panthenol to protect the skin barrier and enhance moisture retention + 8 layers hyaluronic acid complex to provide deep hydration and a bouncy skin. Kaine recently came up with a kombucha serum and it’s just as good, I’ll talk more about it in the next few weeks 

What are your go-to toners at the moment?

latestPosts.caption:
Another day, another comparative review!
@skin1004official Madagascar Centella Ampoule 🆚 Tea-Trica Relief Ampoule, which one is for you? 

🌿 The centella ampoule is formulated with only 7 ingredients, cica being the main and key ingredient. It’s great if you’re dealing with redness, irritation and if you’re looking for a soothing and hydrating product 

🌲 The tea-trica ampoule contains a total of 23 ingredients including about 10% tea tree and 5% cica, and was formulated for acne prone skin, to relieve inflammation and irritation linked to acne, as well as regulate sebum production and help with pore appearance 

I genuinely love these products and you can see them often on my feed. I use the centella ampoule when I am plagued with redness, the tea-trica when I’m breaking out 

Both are free of artificial fragrance & EWG green grade making them suitable for sensitive skin; and the tea-trica is non comedogenic, so safe to use on sensitive-acne prone skin 🤍

Which one would be best for you?

It’s lightweight, fast absorbed and turned out to be even better than any correcting sunscreen or BB cream I own!

The clash of @iunik_official sunscreens ☀️

I love trying out sunscreens, I love iUNIK, so I loved comparing these 2 beautiful formulas! Both are fragrance and EO free, thus suitable for sensitive skin and that’s quite cool 🌀

🌿 Centella Calming Daily sunscreen has been one of my top sunscreens for years (it’s a sad empty as you can see here lol). It works wonders on my dry and redness-prone skin. Super moisturizing, super calming, it’s my go-to when my skin is acting up and I need a “neutral” yet hydrating sunscreen 

🩵 Beta-Glucan Barrier sunscreen is the newest iUNIK launch, perfect for lightweight hydration and barrier care. The formula isn’t always enough for my dry skin, but it’s lovely for summer days and humid environments. It also has an invisible, almost mattifying finish, which oily skin types will appreciate!

Which one would you go for?

latestPosts.caption:
My pre-beach day routine for this summer ☀️🌊

Summer, sea water, and hot days can be rough on the skin, so I love doing a little but mighty hydrating routine beforehand to keep my dry skin as happy as possible 🥰

This line-up is almost entirely new products, recent discoveries I’ve been loving

💙 @isntree hyaluronic acid toner plus
super rich, super viscous, it deeply hydrates my skin and layers so well

💦 @iunik_official beta-glucan power moisture serum contains 40% beta-glucan if my calculations are right, probably the highest percentage I’ve ever seen! Beta-glucan retains up to 20% more moisture than HA, so you can imagine how plumping and hydrating this one is

🎍 @purito_official mighty bamboo panthenol cream, I loved the old version so I was scared to try out this one and be disappointed, but au contraire!! I think I like this new formula even better: just as lightweight, super calming and hydrating

🧡 @purito_official daily soft touch sunscreen (outdoor defense five ceramides) SPF50+ is a new fave! Super lightweight and fast-absorbing, it’s the perfect sunscreen for outdoor activities as it’s water-resistant, sweat-resistant, sand-resistant, and lasts longer than my other sunscreens. Adventure ready!

And that’s it! Simple, but it really helps to minimize water loss during hot days 🔥

Bodrum summer day & reapplying with @alliesofskin ☀️🌊

My love for AoS keeps growing with every new product I try 🥹 I received this gem a couple weeks back and instantly fell for it 

The gel texture is truly unique and almost feels like velvet. It’s fast absorbed, hydrating, non sticky, weightless, and simply invisible once applied 

The inci list is just as lovely: free of fragrance and alcohol, but packed with antioxidants rich plant extracts like aloe vera, green tea, licorice root, carrot seed, pomegranate, raspberry oil & more + staples like vitamin C, vitamin E, & niacinamide

It’s also 80 minutes water and sweat resistant (a must in my humble opinion), suitable for all skin types, and has a real blurring effect that’s almost mattifying!

So yes, yet another hit from Allies of Skin, and now definitely in my top sunscreens of all time 🖤

Thank you @ohmybeloved_official for sending the viral @centellian24_global time reverse madeca cream my way 💫

I’m very happy I got to see for myself what the fuss was all about, and while I love the texture and the general idea of this cream, the scent was a HUGE turn off!

I’m usually not sensitive to fragrance at all, but the night I opened this product the scent literally overwhelmed me! My skin was also a bit sensitive and I thought it was the perfect opportunity to witness their cica technology in action, but it just didn’t work for me 😶

I’m pretty sure I would love this cream if it was fragrance free, or even just a bit toned down lol!

Today’s routine gathers everything my skin needs right now, the 3 N’s 🤍 Let me explain: 

🧊 Neutralize → redness, dark spots, free radicals 🩹 Nurse → damaged barrier, irritation, inflammation 🌱 Nurture → deep hydration, graceful aging, and a soft glow

This routine is packed with skin-loving ingredients: niacinamide & azelaic acid to reduce redness and fade post-acne marks; cica & calming botanicals to soothe inflammation; tranexamic acid to brighten and even out tone; peptides to support regeneration and boost elasticity; panthenol to repair the skin barrier; hyaluronic acid & beta-glucan for deep, lasting hydration… and so much more! 

This line up:  — @caudaliefrance eau de raisin, antioxidants and probiotics in a mist 
— @slurplaboratories niacid, ferments & antioxidants packed for real brightening 
— @anua_global azelaic acid serum to instantly relieve redness 
— @slurplaboratories hyaluid quenches dehydration and supports aging skin
— @marynmay_global TXA + glutathione eye cream to banish dark circles 
— @dr.altheaglobal 345 relief cream for a blemish free and hydrated complexion 
— @purito_official wonder releaf centella daily sun lotion SPF50+ to soothe, hydrate, and protect

I really enjoy this gentle, sensitive skin friendly line up! It brings me back to balance, one layer at a time 🍃
